Key Capabilities
Heuristic Detection System

| Signal            | Weight | Description                                 |
| ----------------- | ------ | ------------------------------------------- |
| Aspect Ratio      | 25%    | Manga pages typically tall (0.6-0.8 ratio)  |
| Image Count       | 20%    | Multiple sequential images indicate gallery |
| Sequential Naming | 15%    | `001.jpg`, `002.jpg` patterns               |
| Vertical Layout   | 15%    | Images stacked vertically                   |
| Text Density      | 10%    | Low text-to-image ratio                     |
| Navigation        | 10%    | Next/prev button patterns                   |
| URL               | 5%     | `/manga/`, `/chapter/` patterns             |


Computer Vision Features
Spatial Clustering: Groups nearby images into reading sequences
Size Consistency: Detects uniform manga page dimensions
Reading Direction: Auto-detects RTL (manga) vs LTR (comics)
Infinite Scroll: Detects and handles dynamic loading
Smart Fallbacks
No selectors needed: Works on any site structure
Confidence scoring: Only activates above 60% probability
Dynamic reanalysis: Adapts to layout changes
Viewport tracking: Estimates current page without explicit indicators
Integration
Extends MangaAdapter base class
Lowest priority (0) in adapter chain
Emits detailed analysis events for debugging
Compatible with all CV/OCR pipelines
This adapter ensures the extension works on any manga site, even those not explicitly supported, by intelligently analyzing page structure and image characteristics.